+## Recommended workflow
+
+The recommended workflow is **count-only**: run `verify_token_counts.py` with no
+benchmark report supplied. This calls only the free count endpoints
+(`messages.count_tokens` for Anthropic, `responses.input_tokens.count` for
+OpenAI) and incurs no chargeable activity.
+
+```bash
+python3 verify_token_counts.py --counts-only
+```
+
+Run `compare_tokens.py` only when you specifically want to validate that the
+free count endpoints match real billed usage. That call costs roughly USD
+0.20–0.30 per full fixture run at current pricing.
+
+## Size tiers
+
+Each case is classified by reported token count:
+
+| Tier | Token range | Purpose |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| probe | < 300 | Edge-case sensitivity. Percentage deltas are unstable. |
+| signal | 300–4000 | Where conclusions come from. Stable percentage deltas. |
+| scaling | > 4000 | Confirms whether deltas grow, shrink, or stay constant. |
+
